As reported in the BBC, "The UK could face major flooding and tropical temperatures by the year 3000 if greenhouse gas emissions are not sharply reduced, a new study says.

The report, from the Tyndall Centre for Climate Change Research, claims Britain could look radically different with sea levels rising as much as 11.4m. "


So, folks, now is your chance! Listen to the British Breakfast on Saturday from 9-11am before it's too late! Do you realise that you've got maybe 1000 years, maybe LESS, to listen to this radio monument to British greatness? Support the UK in this millenium of crisis and listen to the British Breakfast! We will be playing some great music. We like it, and you will too.

Cheers,
Ira from The British Breakfast

Alright, folks, it's official, I can announce it:

Starting the first Saturday (9-11am) in the new year, I will be the new co-host for WRIR's best radio show, The BRITISH BREAKFAST, featuring Britain's best rock music, both new and old. This is 9-11am Saturday mornings on 97.3fm or www.wrir.org.

Also, if you are one of my amazing British mates, you should keep me updated on new bands and whatnot.

Hey, everyone!

Tune in to 97.3 Richmond Indie Radio this Thursday from 5-7pm as I'll be doing Future Perfect! Future Perfect plays all new or unreleased material, and is normally hosted by the Tiny DJ but she's off to Louisiana to rescue animals because they're short on people with rabies vaccines.

I've got an ace show for youm including a LIVE interview and in-studio by one of Richmond's best retro rock bands, THE RACHEL NEVADAS, and an interview with Brit rockers, THE CAPES.

I am terribly sorry (and frustrated) that my show didn't exactly happen tonight. Apparently they were doing maintenance on the building (and didn't tell me) and cut off the electricity half through my first song, which was The Ponys. I called campus police since no one was in the building and they said it'd be off until 10. My CDs are still stuck in the decks there and I wasted gas. Next week if I see any men looking like they are going to steal the radio station's electricity, I swear I'll tackle or bore them to the ground.
